Twenty-two officials of Yobe State Government that returned from Dubai last week have placed themselves on mandatory 14 days’ self-isolation. Some of the returnees confirmed that they are on self-isolation from their families and visitors until the 14 days’ isolation period elapses. The Acting Head of the Civil Service in the State, Mohammed Nura; the Permanent Secretary Ministry of Basic Education and Secondary Education, Yakubu Doskshi; the Special Adviser Political to Governor Mai Mala, Aji Yerima Bularafa all disclosed that they have gone into self-isolation even though none of them was tested positive of the virus on their return.